task.summary: Default task
Components are not instantiated by the broker.
I cannot wrap zeromq sockets in a coroutine. For a reason I don't know it just hangs.
Now aggregation works with multiple keys.
Clarified a little the commenta about the dict comprehension used to distribute the keys previous to the transpose.
Cleaned up unused sentences.
With the new distribution I can clear this todo
Removed all the throttles because they are useless in production.
Deleted the Todo that suggests to remove the zeromq event loop for an asyncio event loop. Even the event loop of pyzmq uses the same mechanism.
Aggregation servers moved from playground to palm_standalone.
Truly parallel test. For some reason, data does not get properly to the aggregator nodes.
The performance and resiliency of the broker has improved by simplifying it, but for some reason it still crashes after lots of messages.
I have changed the broker for a router and it has improved, but it still hangs around 70k messages. Now I have a problem with blosc.
I got to stabilize the aggregation a bit. Now at least it does not return an error complaining that the ctable is not behaving properly. But now the filtering is quite more expensive.
The tests show that for some reason, the push queue for the data accumulation freezes. It wakes up when the aggregation starts.
Speaking my mind. Maybe these queues are not a good idea and should be replaced with router-dealer queues or similar.
Refactored broker for router, which is a better name.
Now it kind of works, and this size is nice for performance tests on a laptop with 2 aggregators.
A lock keeps you from using the dataframe while it is being updated. The dataframe is more memory efficient. The test avoids getting all the keys.
First version of group aggregation implemented and tested.
Improved the example and added serialization for the client.
Replaced key-value pairs by tags.
Transpose does not work. For some reason, the data sent is not always the same, but the job and the data that it is in the database is exactly the same.
The list of companion nodes is wrong at configuration. This causes the transpose to give funny results.

I have problems with connection synchronization and the round robin strategy. Maybe I have to change the req-rep pair of sockets to a pub-sub scheme, so that all sockets can be connected all time, and no message is mistakenly sent.
Merged manually the improvements made at the aggregate_reqrep branch, that has a broken communications model.
Made a more robust transpose using a push-pull queue.
Removed the debugging junk messages. Now the transpose works properly.
Cleaned up.

Changed a lot of things and made it to break absolutely nothing.
Now the API for the szena valuation process is much simple. Now you have a job function that needs the IDN structure and the data for the valuation.
The aggregation is able to get custom keys to label the scenarios, this is provided via the broker key, that now copies the cache variable of the Palm message if it is available. This is a very powerful trick, and it will be used to classify the scenarios in a wide variety of ways. For Szena, the pipeline and the session are the same thing, the same way that the cache and the scenario are too.
The next step is to make the whole system aware of the different scenarios, and support grouping in the aggregation. This will require important changes in the IDN script specification.
Turned the transpose into a container, and removed the object column in the container. Now everything is much faster.
More reasonable test.
Staging. Started the extended client that performs a full aggregation.
This sort of works, but it is not correct. The intersection needs the combinations of the members of the set. You did just an iteration.
The client successfully creates the instrument list according to the groups that are specified.
Improved error messages. I have been playing with it and it seems to work properly.
The filter-by-scenario functionality has been added.
Fixed parameter checking in the scenarios filter function.
Staging. The message flow works, but it still does not implement the aggregation algorithm.
Aggregation works. It returns a json, however.
Now the client does not return a JSON anymore
Made tests a little heavier and prettified the results.
Support for scenario filter. Support for filter chaining. Scenario filters not tested yet.
Version bump. Pylm is now much more stable.
Version bump. Now there's also parallel aggregation.
New version bump. Forgot to specify the version in the pylm dependency.
Fixed an import path needed for the web version of szena.
Added the high level curve to the app.
Updated documentation with the updated IDN specification.
Improved documentation, and chanced the project name.
